00:48:19.810 --> 00:48:23.080 align:middle line:84%
so that absolute value of y sub
n is less than or equal to b.

00:48:23.080 --> 00:48:27.700 align:middle line:84%
But for sequences that are
non-zero and converging

00:48:27.700 --> 00:48:37.330 align:middle line:84%
to a non-zero limit, then you
can bound them away from 0.

00:48:37.330 --> 00:48:39.670 align:middle line:84%
And it's kind of the
same proof that we

00:48:39.670 --> 00:48:43.240 align:middle line:84%
gave for showing that a
convergent sequence is bounded

00:48:43.240 --> 00:48:44.450 align:middle line:90%
above.

00:48:44.450 --> 00:48:48.740 align:middle line:90%
So let me draw a quick picture.

00:48:48.740 --> 00:48:52.238 align:middle line:84%
And let's assume that the
limit is positive just

00:48:52.238 --> 00:48:53.405 align:middle line:90%
for the sake of the picture.

00:48:53.405 --> 00:48:56.010 align:middle line:90%


00:48:56.010 --> 00:48:58.190 align:middle line:84%
So this is a little discussion
on why this is true.

00:48:58.190 --> 00:49:01.885 align:middle line:84%
And this picture
is going to look--

00:49:01.885 --> 00:49:03.260 align:middle line:84%
at least the
explanation is going

00:49:03.260 --> 00:49:08.840 align:middle line:84%
to be kind of similar to
why a sequence is bounded.

00:49:08.840 --> 00:49:14.030 align:middle line:84%
And this one is why
is it bounded below.

00:49:14.030 --> 00:49:17.890 align:middle line:84%
So let's assume that
the limit y is positive.

00:49:17.890 --> 00:49:24.450 align:middle line:84%
And let's say I go
out within distance,

00:49:24.450 --> 00:49:26.920 align:middle line:84%
let's say, y over 2 so
that I'm still positive.

00:49:26.920 --> 00:49:33.510 align:middle line:84%
So this is y minus y
over 2, absolute value.

00:49:33.510 --> 00:49:35.060 align:middle line:84%
So in this picture
y is positive.

00:49:35.060 --> 00:49:38.120 align:middle line:84%
So that's just
equal to y over 2.

00:49:38.120 --> 00:49:39.770 align:middle line:90%
Then what can I say?

00:49:39.770 --> 00:49:49.970 align:middle line:84%
That eventually all of the y sub
n's are here in this interval

00:49:49.970 --> 00:49:50.960 align:middle line:90%
away from 0.

00:49:50.960 --> 00:49:59.620 align:middle line:84%
And, in fact, their absolute
value is bounded by y over 2.

00:49:59.620 --> 00:50:03.220 align:middle line:84%
So let me just
write it that way.

00:50:03.220 --> 00:50:06.880 align:middle line:84%
So all the y sub n's or n
bigger than or equal to some M,

00:50:06.880 --> 00:50:09.580 align:middle line:84%
all have to lie in this interval
because they're converging to y

00:50:09.580 --> 00:50:12.160 align:middle line:90%
and y is positive.

00:50:12.160 --> 00:50:15.220 align:middle line:84%
And therefore in absolute value,
they're all bounded above--

00:50:15.220 --> 00:50:17.260 align:middle line:90%
below I mean-- by y over 2.

00:50:17.260 --> 00:50:21.560 align:middle line:84%
They're all at least
distance y over 2 to 0.

00:50:21.560 --> 00:50:24.350 align:middle line:84%
OK, and then all that's
left to handle are--

00:50:24.350 --> 00:50:30.560 align:middle line:84%
maybe the finitely many
that are left, y sub 1,

00:50:30.560 --> 00:50:38.190 align:middle line:84%
y sub 2, y sub m minus 1, that
are scattered on the real line

00:50:38.190 --> 00:50:39.440 align:middle line:90%
but are non-zero.

00:50:39.440 --> 00:50:40.940 align:middle line:84%
So we're just going
to end up taking

00:50:40.940 --> 00:50:45.242 align:middle line:84%
the minimum of this number
and the absolute value

00:50:45.242 --> 00:50:45.950 align:middle line:90%
of these numbers.

00:50:45.950 --> 00:51:01.780 align:middle line:90%


00:51:01.780 --> 00:51:14.490 align:middle line:84%
So since the y sub n's converge
to y, and y does not equal 0,

00:51:14.490 --> 00:51:24.270 align:middle line:84%
there exist an integer
M such that all n bigger

00:51:24.270 --> 00:51:26.430 align:middle line:84%
than or equal to capital
M. So this picture

00:51:26.430 --> 00:51:28.710 align:middle line:90%
was why this claim is true.

00:51:28.710 --> 00:51:30.810 align:middle line:84%
It was not the proof of
why this claim is true.

00:51:30.810 --> 00:51:32.640 align:middle line:84%
What I'm writing now
is the actual proof

00:51:32.640 --> 00:51:36.440 align:middle line:90%
of why this claim is true--

00:51:36.440 --> 00:51:38.660 align:middle line:84%
such that for all n bigger
than or equal to a capital

00:51:38.660 --> 00:51:46.670 align:middle line:84%
M, y sub n minus y in absolute
value is less than y over 2.

00:51:46.670 --> 00:51:48.920 align:middle line:84%
So for this picture I
drew where y is positive.

00:51:48.920 --> 00:51:50.690 align:middle line:84%
That would have
just been y over 2.

00:51:50.690 --> 00:51:54.410 align:middle line:84%
But you have to use an absolute
value for the other case

00:51:54.410 --> 00:52:00.240 align:middle line:84%
that y is negative, because
this has to b a positive number.

00:52:00.240 --> 00:52:07.960 align:middle line:84%
Then for all n bigger
than or equal to M,

00:52:07.960 --> 00:52:11.080 align:middle line:84%
this any inequality and
the triangle inequality

00:52:11.080 --> 00:52:14.530 align:middle line:84%
gives me-- so if I look at
the absolute value of y,

00:52:14.530 --> 00:52:21.560 align:middle line:84%
this is equal to the absolute
value of y minus y sub n plus y

00:52:21.560 --> 00:52:22.310 align:middle line:90%
sub n.

00:52:22.310 --> 00:52:29.670 align:middle line:84%
And now I use a
triangle inequality,

00:52:29.670 --> 00:52:32.480 align:middle line:84%
which is less than--
this is less than y

00:52:32.480 --> 00:52:37.910 align:middle line:90%
over 2 plus y sub n.

00:52:37.910 --> 00:52:41.060 align:middle line:84%
And I started off with
the absolute value of y .

00:52:41.060 --> 00:52:44.880 align:middle line:84%
So when I subtract
that over, that

00:52:44.880 --> 00:52:49.890 align:middle line:84%
tells me that absolute
value of y over 2

00:52:49.890 --> 00:52:56.320 align:middle line:84%
is less than absolute
value of y sub n for all n

00:52:56.320 --> 00:53:05.670 align:middle line:84%
bigger than or
equal to capital M.

00:53:05.670 --> 00:53:14.820 align:middle line:84%
So then I let to b to be the
minimum of several numbers.

00:53:14.820 --> 00:53:16.830 align:middle line:84%
know I'm writing min,
but I should write inf.

00:53:16.830 --> 00:53:32.420 align:middle line:84%
But so if you like, let me
write inf of y1, Ym minus 1,

00:53:32.420 --> 00:53:37.010 align:middle line:90%
and y over 2.

00:53:37.010 --> 00:53:39.860 align:middle line:84%
And by what you are
doing on the assignment,

00:53:39.860 --> 00:53:43.220 align:middle line:84%
I think it was the
assignment 2, this inf

00:53:43.220 --> 00:53:45.560 align:middle line:90%
always exists in a finite set.

00:53:45.560 --> 00:53:48.980 align:middle line:84%
This is a finite set
of positive numbers.

00:53:48.980 --> 00:53:51.470 align:middle line:84%
And therefore it's
infimum exists

00:53:51.470 --> 00:53:52.670 align:middle line:90%
as one of these elements.

00:53:52.670 --> 00:53:56.870 align:middle line:84%
One of these M numbers
is the infimum.

00:53:56.870 --> 00:53:59.885 align:middle line:84%
And they're all positive, so
this is a positive number.

00:53:59.885 --> 00:54:06.400 align:middle line:90%


00:54:06.400 --> 00:54:10.260 align:middle line:84%
And so then simply how
this number is defined,

00:54:10.260 --> 00:54:22.020 align:middle line:84%
it follows that for all n, y sub
n is bigger than or equal to b.

00:54:22.020 --> 00:54:28.160 align:middle line:90%


00:54:28.160 --> 00:54:31.520 align:middle line:84%
Because, again,
if n is between--

00:54:31.520 --> 00:54:35.060 align:middle line:84%
little n is between 1
and capital M minus 1,

00:54:35.060 --> 00:54:38.570 align:middle line:84%
then certainly that the
absolute value of that thing

00:54:38.570 --> 00:54:43.680 align:middle line:84%
is bigger than or equal to the
smaller of all of these, which

00:54:43.680 --> 00:54:46.000 align:middle line:90%
is bigger than or equal to b.

00:54:46.000 --> 00:54:48.610 align:middle line:84%
And if n is bigger than
or equal to capital M,

00:54:48.610 --> 00:54:51.220 align:middle line:84%
then we proved over
here that y sub n

00:54:51.220 --> 00:54:53.800 align:middle line:84%
is bigger than the
absolute value of y

00:54:53.800 --> 00:54:57.400 align:middle line:84%
over 2, which is bigger
than or equal to the minimum

00:54:57.400 --> 00:55:02.480 align:middle line:84%
of these numbers and y
over 2, which equals b.

00:55:02.480 --> 00:55:03.980 align:middle line:84%
All right, so that
proves the claim.

00:55:03.980 --> 00:55:07.933 align:middle line:90%


00:55:07.933 --> 00:55:08.850 align:middle line:90%
That proves the claim.

00:55:08.850 --> 00:55:10.642 align:middle line:84%
But we haven't proved
what we wanted to yet

00:55:10.642 --> 00:55:13.020 align:middle line:84%
that the limit as n goes to
infinity of 1 over y sub n

00:55:13.020 --> 00:55:15.390 align:middle line:90%
equals 1 over y.

00:55:15.390 --> 00:55:19.680 align:middle line:84%
But this follows
almost immediately

00:55:19.680 --> 00:55:23.280 align:middle line:90%
from what we've done so far.

00:55:23.280 --> 00:55:26.640 align:middle line:84%
So now we're going to use
the claim to prove it.

00:55:26.640 --> 00:55:27.830 align:middle line:90%
So we look at--

00:55:27.830 --> 00:55:33.230 align:middle line:90%


00:55:33.230 --> 00:55:38.060 align:middle line:84%
compute that the 0 is
less than or equal to 1

00:55:38.060 --> 00:55:40.573 align:middle line:90%
over y sub n minus 1 over y.

00:55:40.573 --> 00:55:41.990 align:middle line:84%
We're going to
show that this goes

00:55:41.990 --> 00:55:46.540 align:middle line:90%
to 0 using those two theorems.

00:55:46.540 --> 00:55:51.840 align:middle line:84%
And so by algebra
that's equal to--

00:55:51.840 --> 00:55:56.670 align:middle line:84%
and using the absolute value,
this is 1 over y sub n minus y.

00:55:56.670 --> 00:55:58.620 align:middle line:84%
I mean, the absolute
value of y sub

00:55:58.620 --> 00:56:05.055 align:middle line:84%
n minus y over absolute value
of y sub n absolute value of y.

00:56:05.055 --> 00:56:07.820 align:middle line:90%


00:56:07.820 --> 00:56:11.870 align:middle line:84%
Now y sub n is bigger
than or equal to b.

00:56:11.870 --> 00:56:23.710 align:middle line:84%
So this is less than or equal
to 1 over b times y times

00:56:23.710 --> 00:56:25.180 align:middle line:90%
y sub n minus y.

00:56:25.180 --> 00:56:28.560 align:middle line:90%


00:56:28.560 --> 00:56:32.820 align:middle line:84%
So just to summarize, we've
shown that 0 is less than 1

00:56:32.820 --> 00:56:41.240 align:middle line:84%
over y sub n minus 1 over y
is less than 1 over b times

00:56:41.240 --> 00:56:42.380 align:middle line:90%
1 over--

00:56:42.380 --> 00:56:49.760 align:middle line:84%
b times the absolute value
of y times y sub n minus y.

00:56:49.760 --> 00:56:56.740 align:middle line:84%
Now, this goes to 0 because
it's just a constant sequence.

00:56:56.740 --> 00:57:01.900 align:middle line:84%
This converges to 0 because y
sub n minus y in absolute value

00:57:01.900 --> 00:57:02.950 align:middle line:90%
goes to 0.

00:57:02.950 --> 00:57:05.110 align:middle line:84%
This is just a fixed
number of times that.

00:57:05.110 --> 00:57:12.720 align:middle line:84%
And by what we've proven for
2, this product converges to 0.

00:57:12.720 --> 00:57:23.900 align:middle line:84%
So by the squeeze theorem, we
get that 1 over y sub n, this

00:57:23.900 --> 00:57:26.375 align:middle line:90%
converges to 0, which implies--

00:57:26.375 --> 00:57:32.030 align:middle line:90%


00:57:32.030 --> 00:57:34.350 align:middle line:90%
OK.

00:57:34.350 --> 00:57:37.020 align:middle line:84%
So another big property
about the real numbers

00:57:37.020 --> 00:57:39.840 align:middle line:84%
that we proved after
we stated the existence

00:57:39.840 --> 00:57:43.290 align:middle line:84%
of the real numbers,
which remember was this

00:57:43.290 --> 00:57:45.875 align:middle line:84%
is defined as this ordered
field with a least upper

00:57:45.875 --> 00:57:46.500 align:middle line:90%
bound property.

00:57:46.500 --> 00:57:54.590 align:middle line:90%


00:57:54.590 --> 00:57:57.860 align:middle line:84%
We proved that the square root
of 2 exists as a real number.

00:57:57.860 --> 00:58:01.890 align:middle line:90%


00:58:01.890 --> 00:58:03.980 align:middle line:84%
There was really
nothing special about 2.

00:58:03.980 --> 00:58:08.430 align:middle line:84%
In fact, you could prove
that the square root of x

00:58:08.430 --> 00:58:10.380 align:middle line:84%
exists as a real
number for any x that's

00:58:10.380 --> 00:58:12.990 align:middle line:84%
a positive or
non-negative number.

00:58:12.990 --> 00:58:16.520 align:middle line:90%


00:58:16.520 --> 00:58:18.810 align:middle line:84%
So the square root of a
real number is well defined.

00:58:18.810 --> 00:58:22.738 align:middle line:90%


00:58:22.738 --> 00:58:24.530 align:middle line:84%
Or the square root of
a non-negative number

00:58:24.530 --> 00:58:29.740 align:middle line:84%
is well define and always
exists as a real number.

00:58:29.740 --> 00:58:38.575 align:middle line:84%
So you can ask how does limits
interact with square roots?

00:58:38.575 --> 00:58:41.680 align:middle line:90%


00:58:41.680 --> 00:58:43.810 align:middle line:84%
And they interact just
as you think they should.

00:58:43.810 --> 00:58:53.300 align:middle line:90%


00:58:53.300 --> 00:58:56.030 align:middle line:84%
If I have a sequence
so that for all n,

00:58:56.030 --> 00:59:02.460 align:middle line:84%
x sub n is bigger
than or equal to 0,

00:59:02.460 --> 00:59:06.630 align:middle line:84%
and it's a convergent sequence,
converging to some number x,

00:59:06.630 --> 00:59:14.890 align:middle line:84%
then the limit of the
square roots of these guys

00:59:14.890 --> 00:59:21.050 align:middle line:84%
equals the square
root of the limit, OK.

00:59:21.050 --> 00:59:25.340 align:middle line:84%
Now, I want you to just take
a second here and understand

00:59:25.340 --> 00:59:28.100 align:middle line:84%
that this is a
meaningful statement.

00:59:28.100 --> 00:59:34.840 align:middle line:84%
Because since the x sub n's are
all non-negative by a theorem

00:59:34.840 --> 00:59:35.410 align:middle line:90%
that--

00:59:35.410 --> 00:59:38.310 align:middle line:84%
let's see, did I
erase it already?

00:59:38.310 --> 00:59:46.070 align:middle line:84%
The one that had to deal
with limits and the order,

00:59:46.070 --> 00:59:48.220 align:middle line:84%
so since the x sub n's
are all non-negative,

00:59:48.220 --> 00:59:49.930 align:middle line:84%
