01:00:09.060 --> 01:00:12.160 align:middle line:90%


01:00:12.160 --> 01:00:15.680 align:middle line:90%
So let's prove this.

01:00:15.680 --> 01:00:19.640 align:middle line:84%
So there's two cases to
consider, x is equal to 0

01:00:19.640 --> 01:00:20.810 align:middle line:90%
or x is non-zero.

01:00:20.810 --> 01:00:21.935 align:middle line:90%
So let's do the first case.

01:00:21.935 --> 01:00:26.280 align:middle line:90%


01:00:26.280 --> 01:00:27.570 align:middle line:90%
So the limit is 0.

01:00:27.570 --> 01:00:33.390 align:middle line:84%
So we'll do this proof using
the definition of limits,

01:00:33.390 --> 01:00:37.073 align:middle line:84%
meaning the epsilon
M definition.

01:00:37.073 --> 01:00:39.240 align:middle line:84%
So we want to show that the
limit of the square root

01:00:39.240 --> 01:00:41.700 align:middle line:90%
of x sub n equals 0.

01:00:41.700 --> 01:00:43.410 align:middle line:90%
So let epsilon be positive.

