so that that thing is less

01:01:37.250 --> 01:01:38.567 align:middle line:90%
than what's underneath my hand.

01:01:38.567 --> 01:01:41.150 align:middle line:84%
And the thing that I'm going to
have underneath my hand that's

01:01:41.150 --> 01:01:43.192 align:middle line:84%
going to make things work
out for the square root

01:01:43.192 --> 01:01:46.200 align:middle line:90%
is epsilon squared, OK.

01:01:46.200 --> 01:01:51.230 align:middle line:90%


01:01:51.230 --> 01:01:53.870 align:middle line:90%
Choose M to be M sub 0.

01:01:53.870 --> 01:01:56.550 align:middle line:84%
So I'm going to show this
M works for the sequence

01:01:56.550 --> 01:01:59.630 align:middle line:90%
square root of x sub n.

01:01:59.630 --> 01:02:03.950 align:middle line:84%
And n bigger than or equal
to M. The square root

01:02:03.950 --> 01:02:12.610 align:middle line:84%
